Rating: 3
This is a fine recipe although I must say anyone wanting to make a parsnip dish could come up with this intuitively. It ain't rocket (or culinary) science. That's why I gave it only 3 forks. Agree no need for so much butter. Boiling 30-45 minutes was rather excessive - mine were ready to go in about 15. I really liked all the suggestions by reviewers and will incorporate some of them the next time I make this dish.

Rating: 4
Excellant!!! Butter can be decreased by 3/4 and if you are a Veggie, you can substitute the chicken stock for some of the water you boiled the Parsnips in... Adding roasted garlic really enhances the flavor.

