There were just two of us, so I made a half-recipe. Also, I had planned to make a celery root-pear puree, but then could only find parsnips at the grocery store. The half-recipe plus 2 chopped and sauteed pears in the mix worked out as a great, slightly sweet complement to a blackberry-glazed lamb chop recipe that I found through Google. Yummy!

