I don't think I've ever rated a recipe 4 stars but this was so good and so simple. I made it as a bed for roasted wild mushrooms and finished with a bit of truffle oil. The mushrooms were good, but the parsnips stole the show.

Rating: 3
This is an excellent recipe and simple to make. I substituted Smart Balance for the butter and cut back to about six tablespoons of that. Then, I added two tablespoons chopped scallions at the end to pump it up a bit. I used only about half the parsnips, so you may wish to use more butter or butter substitute. Excellent dish!

